  "market_context": "NQ 4-hour chart where price swept a prior swing low near 24,400 but candle two did not close back inside the previous candle's range, leaving the reversal unconfirmed and requiring additional information from the next candle.",
  "key_observation": "Because candle two failed to produce a reversal closure, the analyst waited for candle three to close over the body of candle two, then used the upper half (above EQ) of candle three's range as the zone for anticipating higher prices.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify that price swept the prior swing low on the NQ 4-hour chart around 24,400.",
    "Check candle two for a reversal closure — observe it did not close back inside the previous candle, so no candle two closure is confirmed.",
    "Wait for the next candle to print to gather more information.",
    "Confirm that candle three closes over the body of candle two, validating a candle three closure reversal.",
    "Mark out the entire range of candle three and identify the upper half (above equilibrium) as the zone for the next candle to trade higher from.",
    "Observe price respects the EQ of candle three and trades higher, closing over the previous candle's high — signalling further continuation."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price respected the equilibrium of candle three and traded higher in the following candle, closing over the prior candle's high and suggesting further continuation.",
  "lessons": "When candle two fails to produce a reversal closure, do not abandon the setup — let candle three print. A candle three closure over candle two's body still validates the reversal, with the upper half (EQ) of candle three serving as the entry zone.",
